ANTIPHON
-
~I have these things that I've been working on. I have this life that I've been doing. Sometimes I think it's all a waste, and it's all an intricate kind of pain. I fear bombardment in the streets, I fear people out there. I try to keep it down, make sure I don't believe myself when someone enters the room and I think they have entered to call me out or punish me in some way. It could be dirty conscience, but I've had it before I did anything wrong. It could be mental illness, but I do not remember having health. And I keep on moving, and falling asleep. And when someone, - a friend, or a foe, or an indifferent commentator, - tells me that I miss opportunities, that I waste time - I feel a mixture of rage and compassion, a cynicism, perhaps. I smile, and I think to myself, "It's the best I can do!"
